<p><a name="Modern_references" id="Modern_references"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ergodic_theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Modern references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Modern references</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFD.V._Anosov2001">D.V. Anosov (2001), <a href="http://eom.springer.de/e/e036150.htm" class="external text" title="http://eom.springer.de/e/e036150.htm" rel="nofollow">"Ergodic theory"</a>, in Hazewinkel, Michiel, <i><a href="/wiki/Encyclopaedia_of_Mathematics" title="Encyclopaedia of Mathematics">Encyclopaedia of Mathematics</a></i>, Kluwer Academic Publishers, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781556080104" class="internal">ISBN 978-1556080104</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Ergodic+theory&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BEncyclopaedia+of+Mathematics%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=D.V.+Anosov&amp;rft.au=D.V.+Anosov&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pub=Kluwer+Academic+Publishers&amp;rft.isbn=978-1556080104&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ergodic_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
